<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>to set a shell environment variable, type the following at the prompt: VARAIBLE_NAME=value

example setting and getting a variable:
&gt;DATE_FORMAT=DMY
&gt;echo $DATE_FORMAT

note, this variable will only be available to the given instance of the shell.  It will not be available on a system reboot or to other instances of the shell.
